The draw for the CAF club competitions quarterfinals was held in Cairo yesterday with the prime tie pairing reigning African kings Al Ahly of Egypt against Morocco’s Raja Casablanca in the Champions League. Two further North African derbies – ES Setif of Algeria v Esperance de Tunis of Tunisia; and CR Belouizdad of Algeria v Wydad Casablanca of Morocco – feature in the premier competition alongside an intriguing clash between Angola’s Petro de Luanda, the surprise package of this season’s CAFCL, and South African heavyweights Mamelodi Sundowns. The winners of the Ahly-Raja tie will face either Setif or Esperance in the semifinals, while Petro or Sundowns will come up against Belouizdad or Wydad on the other side of the draw. The quarterfinals of the Champions League are scheduled to be played on 15-16 and 22-23 April, with the semis on 6-7 and 13-14 May. The final will be played on 29 May at a to-be-determined venue. In the Confederation Cup, Tanzanian heavyweights Simba SC were drawn with South Africa’s Orlando Pirates, Al Ittihad and Al Ahly will meet in a Libyan derby, while Egyptian sides Pyramids FC and Al Masry will come up against TP Mazembe of the DR Congo and RS Berkane of Morocco respectively. The winners of the Libyan derby will face either Simba or Pirates in the semifinals, while the winners of the Pyramids-Mazembe and Masry-Berkane ties will come up against each other on the other side of the draw. The quarterfinals of the Confed Cup are scheduled to be played on 17 and 24 April, with the semis on 8 and 15 May. The date and venue for the final is yet to be announced by CAF.   CAF Champions League quarterfinal draw*   Russia drops appeal on FIFA ban     CAF opens AFCON 2023 office in Abidjan     Tiger Woods ready to play Masters   Al Ahly (Egypt) v Raja Casablanca (Morocco) ES Setif (Algeria) v Esperance de Tunis (Tunisia) Petro de Luanda (Angola) v Mamelodi Sundowns (South Africa) CR Belouizdad (Algeria) v Wydad Casablanca (Morocco)   CAF Confederation